Patience 5 with 50 epochs means training can stop as early as epoch ~30 if SRCC stops improving, potentially missing later gains. Indeed, your logs show SRCC still increasing after epoch 30 (0.8126 -> 0.8896 by epoch 48). If you’d used patience 5 from epoch 31 peak (0.8126), it would have stopped well before the true peak. So the current patience of 5 is clearly too aggressive given the long upward trend.

We need to look at the actual improvement trajectory: the model improves steadily until epoch ~40, then fluctuates. Patience 10 would have allowed it to keep going. I’d argue patience=10 is a fix, not just a may‑fix.

Interactions: If we add a LR scheduler that decays LR, the metric might still improve slowly over many epochs, so a longer patience is needed.

Verdict: Fix for baseline – increase patience to 10 or even 12. Also save best model based on combined SRCC+PLCC.

